    "Therefore, it also has linearised Lipschitz non-regularity and weak Lipschitz non-regularity.We actually also prove linearised Lipschitz non-regularity more \"directly\" (it follows immediately from Theorem 5.24 together with Baire category theorem, or from Corollary 5.25 together with the fact that strong non-surjectivity implies non-surjectivity; cf.",
    "Section 4).Before we discuss some aspects of the proof, we discuss related results in literature.",
